annotate.velvetConfig: provides information regarding Velvet instance to be used by application: host sets url on which the velvet instance is exposed, apikey for authorize client application and productId used as default Carbon Product ID in communication with Velvet
annotate.globals: this is a collection of global accessible objects, each object in this collection can be used in any angular expression in Lynx application (objects can be provided by value or by factory)
annotate.AuthModel: object lynx.models.AuthModel is dedicated in Lynx framework to be used for authentication purposes; it is instantiated by factory method as all Lynx global objects provide factory method
annotate.authMode: Velvet switch for setting authentication algorithm; supported modes are BASIC and RC4Token
annotate.$auth: model instance of lynx.models.AuthModel object is exposed under $auth alias to any expression; you may create multiple instances of the same model type each binded to different aliases
